com.fasterxml.util.membuf

Interface StreamyMemBuffer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, MemBuffer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StreamyBytesMemBuffer, StreamyBytesMemBufferImpl, StreamyLongsMemBuffer, StreamyLongsMemBufferImpl, StreamyMemBufferBase

    public interface StreamyMemBuffer
extends MemBuffer
    Generic type for MemBuffers that store data as contiguous sequence of primitive values, so units of appending and reading do not necessarily match. This is similar to JDK stream abstraction.

    Note that most actual read and append methods are defined in type-specific subtypes (such as StreamyBytesMemBuffer), since Java does not have a way to define generic primitive types.
